/**********************************************************************
 * File:    machine/package.doc
 * Purpose: Describe input of packages
 * Author:  Karl Abrahamson
 **********************************************************************/

When a package is read in by package.c, it is
put into an array of unsigned characters.  
The description of the package currently being read in is in
current_pack_params.  package_descr[n] holds a description of package
number n, in somewhat less detail. 


Functions for getting packages are

read_package(s)		Reads package s, if it has not already been read.

read_to_end(f)		Reads instructions from file f into the package 
			until an END_I instruction is seen.

do_patches()		Fix up forward label references.

init_package_reader()	Should be called when starting interpreter.

index_at_label(n)	Returns the index stored at global label n.

index_at_addr(s)	Gets the integer n at address *s, moves *s just 
			beyond that integer, and returns the integer
			at address *s + n.  Used to get an index whose index
			is in the code.

